records.addlTxt:
Defendant Devonta R Edwards in court with attorney Reyna Ivonne Morales.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.

AS TO BOTH COUNTS:  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.

Defendant sentenced to serve 90 days in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to each other with credit for 8 days time served as to Count 1; STRAIGHT TIME.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 year.
CONDITIONS AS TO BOTH COUNTS:
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Maintain absolute sobriety to be monitored by random urine screens;
*  Maintain full time employment;
*  Cooperate with agent;
*  Submit a DNA sample;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.

CONDITIONS AS TO COUNT 1 ONLY:
*  Perform 20 hours of community service.

If the defendant successfully completes all conditions of probation, the Court will grant expungement.  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
